    • Method Detail

      • setInventory

        public void setInventory​(Inventory inventory)
        This method passes the inventory from the main form into the controller for the part form.
        Parameters:
        inventory - The inventory we are adding parts to (static from main form).

      • setHomeController

        public void setHomeController​(Controller controller)
        This method passes the controller from the main form into the controller for the part form. Passing the main form controller into this controller will allow us to update tables in the main form.
        Parameters:
        controller - The main form's controller, used to pass back information.

      • setPartToModify

        public void setPartToModify​(Part part)
        If we are modifying a part, this method is used to pass that part into the controller.
        Parameters:
        part - The part we are modifying if we are modifying a part (as opposed to adding a new part).

      • handleSavePart

        public void handleSavePart()
        Checks if input is valid and saves the part to the inventory. This is used for adding new parts as well as modifying existing parts.

      • inputIsValid

        private boolean inputIsValid()
        Method used for validating input on the form.
        Returns:
        True if form input is valid, false if input is invalid.

      • inventoryIsValid

        private boolean inventoryIsValid​(boolean inputIsValid)
        Method used for validating inventory data.
        Parameters:
        inputIsValid - A boolean indicating if the form input was valid.
        Returns:
        True if form inventory data is valid, false if inventory data is invalid.

      • handleCancelPart

        public void handleCancelPart()
        Method for the "cancel" button on the form. Responsible for closing the form when user cancels a part entry/modification.

      • setModifyParts

        public void setModifyParts​(boolean modifyParts)
        Method responsible for defining whether or not we are adding a new part or modifying an existing part.
        Parameters:
        modifyParts - A boolean value that indicates if we are modifying parts, (false for adding new parts).

      • inHouseChecked

        public void inHouseChecked()
        Checks to see if in-house radio button is selected. Updates form based on which radio button is selected.

      • outsourcedChecked

        public void outsourcedChecked()
        Checks to see if outsourced radio button is selected. Updates form based on which radio button is selected.
